special_powers.description: The Flash can use Super Senses, but succeeds on a roll of 3-6. This roll can't be rerolled.

special_powers.name: GINGOLD SODA
special_powers.description: Elongated Man can use Plasticity. Opposing characters within 2 squares and line of fire treat Elongated Man as adjacent for movement purposes.

special_powers.name: CLOSING IN ON A SUSPECT
special_powers.description: Elongated Man can use Barrier, Combat Reflexes, and Willpower.

special_powers.name: MY NOSE IS TWITCHING
special_powers.description: Elongated Man can use Outwit as if he had a range value of 8 and Improved Targeting: Elevated, Hindering, Characters.

special_powers.name: LAST STRIPED TIGER OF KHANDAQ
special_powers.description: At the beginning of the game, place a Tawny bystander token as described on this card adjacent to Captain Thunder. Give Captain Thunder a free action when he has two action tokens and place a friendly character within 8 squares and line of fire named Tawny adjacent to him.

special_powers.name: YOU WOULDN'T HURT A BUNCHA ORPHANS?
special_powers.description: Captain Thunder can use Shape Change and Super Senses. When this power is revealed due to taking damage from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial and remove all action tokens from Captain Thunder. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: SHAZAM!
special_powers.description: Captain Thunder can use Pulse Wave with a range value of 6. When he does and he targets more than one character, his damage value becomes 2 and is locked. When he uses Pulse Wave and actions resolve you may choose to deal Captain Thunder 1 unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: SPEED FORCE
special_powers.description: When Professor Zoom moves at least one square and hits one or more adjacent characters, you may place a Speed token on this card after actions resolve. Increase Professor Zoom's speed value by the number of Speed tokens on this card.

special_powers.name: RETURN OF BARRY ALLEN
special_powers.description: If Professor Zoom has at least 2 Speed tokens on this card, he can use Shape Change and Willpower. If Professor Zoom has at least 3 Speed tokens on this card, he can use Blades/Claws/Fangs with a close combat attack and Sidestep. If he has at least 4 Speed tokens on this card, he deals penetrating damage when making an attack.

special_powers.name: RETURN FROM THE FUTURE
special_powers.description: If Professor Zoom has 10 Speed tokens on this card or more, you may remove them all to take one extra turn after this one.

special_powers.name: ALTER YOUR TIMELINE
special_powers.description: Professor Zoom can use Combat Reflexes. Once per attack, when Professor Zoom takes damage from an attack and this click is revealed, you may deal Professor Zoom's printed damage value to the attacking character if you remove a Speed token from this card. If you remove 2 Speed tokens instead, this damage is penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: SPEED FORCE
special_powers.description: When Zoom moves at least one square and hits one or more adjacent characters, you may place a Speed Token on this card after actions resolve. Increase Zoom's speed value by the number of Speed Tokens on this card.

special_powers.name: A NEW BLACK FLASH
special_powers.description: Remove a Speed token from this card and choose either Exploit Weakness or Flurry. If you do, Zoom can use Blades/Claws/Fangs and the chosen power as a free action instead of making a close combat attack while using Hypersonic Speed this turn.

special_powers.name: YOU FIGHT ME AS IF I LIVE
special_powers.description: Zoom can use Regeneration and Toughness. When he uses Regeneration, increase the result of the d6 roll by half the number of Speed Tokens on this card. Maximum 6.

special_powers.name: DEATH: WILL MAKE YOU BETTER
special_powers.description: Zoom can use Steal Energy. When an opposing character is KO'd, heal Zoom of 1 damage and place a Speed token on this card.

special_powers.name: PUPPET TRANSFORMATION
special_powers.description: When an opposing character targets Abra Kadabra with an attack and misses, that character has "tiny damage symbol" and modifies its attack and damage values by -1. This effect lasts until that character begins and ends the same turn with no action tokens.

special_powers.name: SELLING THE SOULS OF OTHERS
special_powers.description: Give Abra Kadabra a free action and deal 1 unavoidable damage to another friendly character that shares a keyword with Abra Kadabra and is within range and line of fire. When you do, choose any one standard power and Abra Kadabra can use that power until your next turn.

special_powers.name: MASTER MAGICIAN
special_powers.description: Abra Kadabra can use Perplex and Shape Change.

special_powers.name: SPEED STEALER
special_powers.description: Give Cobalt Blue a free action and choose any number of target opposing characters within 8 squares and line of fire. Until your next turn those characters modify their speed values by -3 and Cobalt Blue modifies his speed value by +1 for each character targeted this way and his attack value by +1 for every two targeted this way.

special_powers.name: A TERRIBLE SWIFT SWORD
special_powers.description: Cobalt Blue can use Exploit Weakness. Adjacent opposing characters can't use Shape Change or Super Senses.

special_powers.name: A FLAME THAT CHILLS, NOT BURNS
special_powers.description: When Cobalt Blue makes a close combat attack against a single target and actions resolve, roll a d6. On a result of 4-6, give the target an action token.

special_powers.name: PROVE I'M THE STRONGEST MIND
special_powers.description: When Gorilla Grodd is targeted by Mind Control, Outwit, Penetrating/Psychic Blast, or Perplex, both you and that character's player must roll a d6 that can't be rerolled. If your result is higher, Gorilla Grodd can't be targeted by that power this turn.

special_powers.name: ANIMAL FURY
special_powers.description: Gorilla Grodd can use Charge and Flurry.

special_powers.name: MASTER THE MIND, DESTROY THE MIND
special_powers.description: Gorilla Grodd can use Mind Control and Penetrating/Psychic Blast. When he uses Mind Control and hits all targets, after actions resolve he can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast as a free action. Gorilla Grodd isn't dealt unavoidable damage from Mind Control.

special_powers.name: ATTRACT OR REPEL
special_powers.description: Give Magenta a free action and choose a character with "standard damage symbol" or "tiny damage symbol" within 3 squares and line of fire.  Place that character into a square adjacent to the one they currently occupy.

special_powers.name: RIDING THE MAGNETIC FIELDS
special_powers.description: Magenta can use Telekinesis.  Give Magenta a move action and, after actions resolve, she can use Telekinesis as a free action.

special_powers.name: MAGNETIC BARRIERS
special_powers.description: Magenta can use Barrier and Toughness.  When she uses Barrier and actions resolve, you may choose one opposing character with "standard attack symbol" and "standard damage symbol" within 2 squares of a blocking terrain marker that she has placed and place that character adjacent to the marker.  When a character adjacent to one of these markers attempts to move, it must attempt to break away as if the marker was a character friendly to Magenta and can't be ignored for movement purposes.

special_powers.name: TAKE THEIR VESSEL!
special_powers.description: Deathstroke can use Leap/Climb and Stealth. When Deathstroke hits a character that can use the Carry ability, after actions resolve he can use Mind Control targeting that character as a free action.

special_powers.name: STEAL MORE THAN YOUR GOLD
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, you may choose a standard damage power that an opposing character within 6 squares possesses. Deathstroke can use that power and the opposing character can't use it until your next turn.

special_powers.name: POWER OF THE DARKLANDS
special_powers.description: Shade can use Smoke Cloud and Stealth. If he has 2 action tokens, he can use Smoke Cloud as a free action.

special_powers.name: SHADOW DEMONS
special_powers.description: Before removing Shade's hindering terrain markers from the map, deal 1 damage to each opposing character within range occupying one of those markers. If that character is also adjacent to 2 or more of Shade's hindering terrain markers, the damage dealt is penetrating.

special_powers.name: HERO? VILLIAN? WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?
special_powers.description: Shade can use Perplex. When he does, he may immediately choose a friendly character of 50 points or more and modify that character's combat values by -1 until your next turn, and then use it a second time.

special_powers.name: 9 PINTS OF LIQUID MACHINERY FOR BLOOD
special_powers.description: Give Engineer a free action and choose a standard speed, attack, and damage power. She can use those powers until her next turn.

special_powers.name: TOXIC ENVIRONMENT CLEANSE
special_powers.description: If an opposing character would use Poison to deal penetrating damage or more than 1 damage, they deal 1 damage instead.

special_powers.name: ELECTRICAL CORTEX SHORT CIRCUIT
special_powers.description: When Jenny Sparks hits an opposing character, that character can't use special powers from now until your next turn.

special_powers.name: MASSIVE ELECTRICAL ARC
special_powers.description: Jenny Sparks can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast, Improved Targeting: Characters, and has "3 bolts". When she uses Penetrating/Psychic Blast, increase the damage dealt to each hit character by the number of characters adjacent to it.

special_powers.name: IF YOU DIE, I'LL JUST DIG YOU UP AND PUT YOU TO WORK AGAIN
special_powers.description: Jenny Sparks can use Leadership. When she does and the result is 6, remove all action tokens from all adjacent friendly characters with the Authority keyword.

special_powers.name: BOUND BY SIN
special_powers.description: For each other friendly character with the Trinity of Sin or Warrior keyword modify Pandora's range value by +1 and increase the number of "bolt" she possesses by 1.

special_powers.name: OPENING THE EVILS
special_powers.description: Pandora can use Poison. When she does, characters are instead dealt damage equal to 1 plus the number of action tokens they are assigned.

special_powers.name: PURGING MY SINS
special_powers.description: Pandora can use Perplex. When she has two action tokens and uses it to target an opposing character, remove an action token from her.

special_powers.name: WK D-T001 TRINITY OF SIN
special_powers.description: This team character can use Precision Strike and modifies their range value by +2.

special_powers.name: BOUND BY SIN
special_powers.description: Phantom Stranger can use Phasing/Teleport and the Carry ability but his speed value is not modified by it. He may carry one additional character for each other friendly character with the Mystical or Trinity of Sin keyword.

special_powers.name: MYSTICAL MANIPULATOR
special_powers.description: Phantom Stranger can use Mind Control and the Mystics team ability. He may use Mind Control as a free action to target a single opposing character with two action tokens.

special_powers.name: I WALKED WITH THE LAMB
special_powers.description: Phantom Stranger can use Defend, Invulnerability, and Mastermind. When Phantom Stranger transfer damage using Mastermind, he can choose to only transfer some of it. If he does, any damage not transferred is dealt to him as unavoidable damage.

special_powers.name: PURGING MY SINS
special_powers.description: Phantom Stranger can use Probability Control. When he has 2 action tokens and uses it during an opponent's turn, remove an action token from him.

special_powers.name: WK D-T001 TRINITY OF SIN
special_powers.description: When this team character has no action tokens, they can use Steal Energy. When they have one action token, they can use Regeneration.

special_powers.name: BOUND BY SIN
special_powers.description: The Question can use Toughness and is a wild card. The Question may copy an uncopyable team ability from a character with the Detective or Trinity of Sin keyword.

special_powers.name: WHAT OF MY SINS?
special_powers.description: The Question can use Charge, Shape Change and Stealth.

special_powers.name: BINARY GAS
special_powers.description: The Question may use Poison and Precision Strike. When he uses Poison or makes an attack, after actions resolve, he can use Smoke Cloud as a free action, but only to place hindering terrain tokens in a square he occupies or is adjacent to.

special_powers.name: PURGING MY SINS
special_powers.description: The Question can use Outwit. When he does, remove an action token from him if he has 2 action tokens.

special_powers.name: WK D-T001 TRINITY OF SIN
special_powers.description: This team character can use Shape Change and Stealth.

special_powers.name: SPEED FORCE
special_powers.description: When The Flash moves at least one square and hits one or more adjacent characters, you may place a Speed token on this card after actions resolve. Increase The Flash's speed value by the number of Speed tokens on this card.

special_powers.name: BLESSINGS OF MERCURY
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Sidestep. When he does, his locked speed value is 2 plus the number of Speed tokens on this card, instead of 2.

special_powers.name: MOVING TOO FAST
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Hypersonic Speed. When he hits an opposing character, it generates knock back and the character is knocked back 2 squares for every click of damage it takes.

special_powers.name: NOW I'VE GOT IT!
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Quake. The Flash can use it normally or he can use it instead of a close combat attack.

special_powers.name: SPEED FORCE
special_powers.description: When The Flash moves at least one square and hits one or more adjacent characters, you may place a Speed token on this card after actions resolve. Increase The Flash's speed value by the number of Speed tokens on this card.

special_powers.name: SWIFTER THAN THE RAPIDITY OF THOUGHT
special_powers.description: If The Flash has at least 1 Speed token on this card, his combat values can't be modified by opposing characters. If he has at least 3 Speed tokens on this card, his powers can't be countered.

special_powers.name: RUNNING LAPS AROUND THE WORLD
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Hypersonic Speed. Remove a Speed token from this card and once this turn, The Flash may consider squares on edges of the map to be adjacent to each other for movement purposes, as long as they are in the same row or column.

special_powers.name: FASTER THAN...WELL, PRETTY MUCH ANYTHING
special_powers.description: The Flash can use Willpower. Increase his defense value by the number of Speed tokens on this card.

special_powers.name: SPEED FORCE
special_powers.description: When Max Mercury moves at least one square and hits one or more adjacent characters, you may place a Speed token on this card after actions resolve. Increase Max Mercury's speed value by the number of Speed tokens on this card.

special_powers.name: WHIP WHIRLWIND
special_powers.description: Give Max Mercury a free action and remove 1 Speed token from this card; when you do Max Mercury can use Quake and his attack value becomes equal to his speed value until he removes another Speed token.

special_powers.name: WINDRUNNER
special_powers.description: Give Max Mercury a free action and remove 1 Speed token from this card; when you do Max Mercury can use Toughness and his defense value becomes equal to his speed value plus 7 until he removes another Speed token.

special_powers.name: QUICKSILVER
special_powers.description: Give Max Mercury a free action and remove 2 Speed tokens from this card. When he does, Max Mercury can use Outwit and doubles his speed value until he removes another Speed Token.

special_powers.name: LAW ENFORCEMENT CONSULTANT
special_powers.description: When building your force, all characters with the Police keyword have the Central City keyword.

special_powers.name: POLICE INFORMANT
special_powers.description: When Central City Police Captain is adjacent to a friendly character with the Central City keyword, Central City Police Captain can use Outwit but only as a power action.

special_powers.name: POLICE TACTICAL PLAN
special_powers.description: Central City Police Captain can use Leadership, but only to remove an action token from an adjacent character with the Police keyword regardless of point value.

special_powers.name: GREEN ROOM; DIMENSIONAL TESSERACTS
special_powers.description: Give A.R.G.U.S Researcher a power action. This turn, A.R.G.U.S Reseacher can use Improved Targeting: Elevated, Blocking and friendly characters' range values are a minimum of 8 when using Outwit, Perplex, or Probability Control.

special_powers.name: LIFE & DEATH & BEYOND
special_powers.description: If Captain Boomerang is 115 points, he begins the game on his green starting line. If Captain Boomerang is 55 points, he begins on either his green or red starting line and is KO'd normally or if he crosses a red KO line.

special_powers.name: DEATH: RETURN TO ME
special_powers.description: Captain Boomerang can use Steal Energy with close or ranged combat attacks. When an opposing character is KO'd, heal Captain Boomerang of 1 damage and remove an action token from him.

special_powers.name: INTANGIBLE
special_powers.description: Golden Glider can use Phasing/Teleport.

special_powers.name: INDUCED HEART ATTACK
special_powers.description: Golden Glider can use Poison. At the beginning of your turn choose an adjacent opposing character; all damage dealt to that character this turn is penetrating.

special_powers.name: YOUR FAMILIES ARE MY HOSTAGES
special_powers.description: When Rag Doll is KO'd by an opponent's attack, that character modifies its attack value by -2 for the rest of the game, even if this ability is lost.

special_powers.name: CULT LEADER
special_powers.description: Rag Doll can use Exploit Weakness, Leadership, and Outwit.

special_powers.name: KNOCK THEM DOWN
special_powers.description: When an adjacent opposing character takes 2 or more damage from Gorilla City Commander's attack and that attack didn't generate knockback, the target is then knocked back 2 squares and then given an action token.

special_powers.name: GROWING OUR RANKS
special_powers.description: When this character takes damage from an opponent's attack, roll a d6 after actions resolve.  On a result of 5-6, you may place adjacent to this character FL #210 Mob Rule on click #3 -or- FL #009 Mob Rule on the click #1 that appears after the orange KO.

Give a character occupying this square a power action and roll 2d6 that can't be rerolled. Add that character's printed speed value and if the result is 20 or higher, remove an action token from each character on your force and this character can use Probability Control this turn.
